related_questions.question: Who should not take ginger?
related_questions.snippet: Pregnant or breastfeeding women, people with heart conditions, and people with diabetes should not take ginger without talking to their doctors. DO NOT take ginger if you have a bleeding disorder or if you are taking blood-thinning medications, including aspirin.

buttons.snippet: Place the rhizomes about an inch deep in warm soil (whether in a container or in the ground, ginger grows only when soil temperature is over 68ºF and grows best with soil temperatures around 77ºF) with the growth buds pointing upward. Water lightly until growth begins.
